TREASURY'S AUCTION SCHEDULE IS MINIMAL 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Monday's regular weekly auction of three- and six-month bills. By
the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders said, the
rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.41 percent and a
six-month bill was 4.74 percent.
</P>
