<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-06 20:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5027 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      06-06 0494
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Monday, June 7,
and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Veronica
Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSING-WORKERS (Seattle) _ Joe Soroka survived the move from
the moderately priced and stable housing market of Cleveland to the
increasingly pricey housing market in the Seattle area. All it took
was a ``sizable salary increase to be motivated to come out here,''
the banker says _ and a willingness to commute 30 miles each day
from North Bend, Wash., to downtown Seattle. High prices,
especially for housing, haven't stopped people from coming. But
costly housing is making it increasingly difficult to recruit
employees to the region, employers say.
</P>
<P>
   By Bill Virgin and Tracy Johnson. (Story will move in the ``a''
and ``f'' categories.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-SEATTLE FESTIVAL (Seattle) _ ``Run Lola Run,'' an
exhilarating German film about a woman frantically trying to raise
money to pay off her boyfriend's debt to gangsters, received the
Golden Space Needle award for best picture Sunday in the closing
ceremonies of the 25th Seattle International Film Festival. Wrapup
on the Film Festival.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-FIELDING _ Single women on both sides of the Atlantic fell
head over heels over ``Bridget Jones's Diary'' by Helen Fielding,
turning this comic novel of singlehood into a huge best seller. A
visit in Seattle with British author Fielding, in America to
promote the paperback release.
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-SOPRANOS (Undated) _ If you don't have HBO and you don't have
a friend/relative/neighbor who has HBO and you're just waiting for
a legitimate reason to have HBO, ``The Sopranos'' is probably it.
Shoot, the performance of James Gandolfini alone is worth the cost
of subscribing.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-OWEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ As a kid, I prowled what we called
Skid Row in Great Falls, Mont., on my paper route. Can you imagine
parents today sending their kids into the roughest part of town at
5 in the morning? No, you can't. But I supplied the morning papers
on Skid Row and what I got from the residents in return were
smiles, waves and an occasional invitation to partake of a free
hamburger.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story ha moved in the ``d'' category.)
</P>
