<HEADLINE>
MYERS MAKES GALAXY DEBUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Costa Rican midfielder Roy Myers made his Los
Angeles Galaxy debut Sunday. Myers was dealt to Los Angeles from
New York/New Jersey in a three-team deal that sent Welton to Miami
earlier in the week.
</P>
<P>
   Myers replaced Ezra Hendrickson on the right side of the
midfield to start the second half and left a good impression with
Galaxy coach Sigi Schmid.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was good, I was very happy with him,'' said Schmid. ``He's
got a great attitude and he's a very sneaky defensive player.''
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy has had trouble maintaining possession, but Myers is
known for his ability to make good passes.
</P>
<P>
   ``He sent a couple of good balls in for people to get sprung on
breakaways,'' said Schmid. ``And he also found (Mauricio)
Cienfuegos which is something we're always trying to do. I think as
he gets more comfortable with our team he's going to become an
important part.''
</P>
<P>
   Hermosillo's return: The Galaxy is hoping to get a scoring lift
when Mexican scoring champion Carlos Hermosillo joins the team
Monday after finishing his season in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Hermosillo is coming at a good time. The Galaxy faces MLS
champion Chicago Saturday at the Rose Bowl without Cobi Jones and
Robin Fraser. Both Jones and Fraser will be with the U.S. National
team when they face Argentina in Chicago the same day.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had about six or seven good crosses and a couple of good
crosses on corners that we didn't do anything with today,'' said
Schmid. ``That's where Hermosillo is going to help us.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's also pretty strong on the ball. He's tough to muscle
around and he's got a good spin with defenders on him. Those are
just a couple of dimensions he brings and those are certainly
area's where we have struggled.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-06-99 2220EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
